I'd generally echo Ben's suggestions.

In particular, it is likely useful to time sections of objective calculation with
microbenchmark. My experience is that only some sections of objective are critical,
so only parts need be coded outside R. Sometimes changing to different R code can
be enough. Ben didn't mention Fortran. Now getting old-fashioned, but it can be
very fast for some operations, but be careful to count the call and return i.e.,
time outside the replaced objective code, not just inside the sub-programs.

About 10 years ago managed to get better than 10* speedup with approach replacing
"bits and pieces"

Cheers, JN


