Hi, Rich:


Thanks for the detail.


Have you tried to use MediaWiki Extension:Chart?[3]


It looks to me like it already works. It includes a few examples including some in Wikimedia Commons "Category:Data:Examples.chart".[4]
That page includes a "Discussion" page, where you could lobby for resurrecting MediaWiki "Extension:R".


I'm guessing that they decided NOT to maintain it, because it had been available for years, and was used so little, the MediaWiki management could not justify the cost of maintaining it.


If it has been used in an internal NASA Wiki, you might be able to find someone inside NASA capable of making it work locally. If so, then you could offer the new code to MediaWiki with documentation on why it's valuable and how to use it. I could help you develop post tutorials to an internal NASA Wiki on how to use it. Then if MediaWiki executives agree to maintain it after you have it work, I will happily help you port the tutorials to Wikiversity ;-)


sg


